Journals

  

 Computers, Environment and Urban Systems (CEUS) is housed here in the center, with Grubesic serving as the Editor-in-Chief.  CEUS is an interdisciplinary journal publishing cutting-edge and innovative computer-based research on urban systems, systems of cities, and built and natural environments, that privileges the geospatial perspective. 

For more information, see: https://www.journals.elsevier.com/computers-environment-and-urban-systems

International Regional Science Review (IRSR) is also housed in the center, with Grubesic serving as Co-Editor-in-Chief.  IRSR is a forum  for  geographers, economists, regional scientists, planners and other social scientists to share important research findings and methodological breakthroughs that have a spatial dimension. 

For more information, see: http://journals.sagepub.com/home/irx

Lastly, Grubesic serves as Editor-in-Chief for Telematics and Informatics (TELE).  TELE is an interdisciplinary journal examining the social, economic, political and cultural impacts and challenges of information and communication technologies.

For more information, see: https://www.journals.elsevier.com/telematics-and-informatics
